  "overridesNotes": {
    "epubjs/@xmldom/xmldom": "epubjs@0.3.93 declares '@xmldom/xmldom: ^0.7.5', but the entire 0.7.x line is upstream-deprecated and the < 0.8.12 range is affected by GHSA (CDATA terminator injection) reported by Dependabot. We override to the patched 0.8.x line. This is verified safe because (1) epubjs only uses @xmldom/xmldom as a Node/IE fallback in src/utils/core.js and src/section.js, both guarded by `typeof DOMParser === 'undefined'` / `typeof XMLSerializer === 'undefined' || isIE`, so the code path is dead in modern browsers (TerminusEbook.vue does not pass forceXMLDom); (2) the only APIs invoked are DOMParser#parseFromString and XMLSerializer#serializeToString, whose surface is stable across 0.7.x and 0.8.x; (3) upstream epubjs@0.5.0-alpha.x itself depends on '@xmldom/xmldom: ^0.8.2', confirming forward compatibility for the same usage pattern.",
    "tar": "Force all transitive copies of tar to >=7.5.4 to fix Dependabot advisory #485 (GHSA — race condition in node-tar path reservations via Unicode ligature collisions on macOS APFS; vulnerable range <=7.5.3, patched 7.5.4). Without this override, four nested copies remain in the lockfile (under @electron/node-gyp, @electron/rebuild, app-builder-lib, cacache) at tar@6.2.1, all in scope of the advisory. Dependabot's original PR #1099 attempted to upgrade ancestor electron-builder 26.0.12 -> 26.8.1 but was auto-closed by the bot itself. This override is dev-scope only (electron build/release toolchain, not shipped at runtime). tar@7 requires Node >=18 (we run Node 20), and the only API surface used by these consumers (Pack/Unpack via streaming entries) is stable across tar 6 -> 7; the 7.x default-flip on `chmod` is harmless for npm-tarball/ICONV-style extraction targets. Top-level tar in the lockfile was already at 7.5.x prior to this override, confirming the toolchain handles tar@7 without issue.",
    "@tootallnate/once": "@tootallnate/once <2.0.0 (i.e. 1.x) is affected by GHSA-c2qf-rxjj-qqgw (ReDoS). Override to ^2.0.0 to evict any 1.x copy from the lockfile while staying on the CommonJS line. Do NOT bump to 3.x: 3.0.0+ is published as ESM-only ('type: module', no CJS export), but the dev-toolchain chain make-fetch-happen -> http-proxy-agent@5.x is still CommonJS and loads it via require('@tootallnate/once'). With a 3.x override Node throws ERR_REQUIRE_ESM during node-gyp / electron-builder header download and native rebuild, breaking linux/macos/windows CI (observed: bcrypt rebuild fails for Electron 39.8.x). Once http-proxy-agent across the toolchain is upgraded to >=6 (which drops @tootallnate/once for agent-base), this override can be removed."
  },
  "overrides": {
    "dunder-proto": "1.0.1",
